  "title": "QA Lab Technician (Metallurgy & Material Inspection)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Prepare and evaluate metallurgical samples; generate detailed reports.</li>\n  <li>Inspect incoming materials for quality compliance.</li>\n  <li>Maintain lab inventory and ensure proper housekeeping (6S).</li>\n  <li>Assist with calibration and record management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Nitec in Precision Engineering, Aerospace Machining, or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years’ experience in <strong>MRO QA or related lab environment.</strong></li>\n  <li>Proficient with measuring tools like <strong>callipers and micrometres.</strong></li>\n  <li>Basic understanding of <strong>GD&amp;T drawings.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at<strong> </strong><a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
